# Admin Dashboard

## Identity

This is the **operator management dashboard** for the Litecoin Knowledge Hub. It is used by administrators to monitor system health, manage caches, review knowledge gaps, and configure abuse prevention. It is NOT the public chat interface.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Framework | Next.js | 16.0.9 |
| React | React | 19.2.1 |
| UI Components | Radix UI primitives | (NO Shadcn — no `components.json`) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | v4 |
| Icons | Lucide React | latest |
| Utilities | clsx, tailwind-merge | latest |

## Key Conventions

### UI Components

Components in `components/ui/` are **hand-rolled Radix primitives** — NOT Shadcn. There is no `components.json`, no Shadcn CLI. Do not run `npx shadcn-ui` in this project. Do not assume `cn()` utility or Shadcn component APIs.

When adding new UI primitives, build them from Radix directly following the patterns in existing `components/ui/` files.

### Authentication

Bearer token auth stored in `localStorage` as `admin_token`:

- Login: `POST /api/v1/admin/auth/login` → receives token
- Verification: `GET /api/v1/admin/auth/verify` with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`
- Protection: `AuthGuard` component wraps all protected routes, redirects to `/` (login) on auth failure

### API Client

`lib/api.ts` is the centralized API client. All calls go **directly to the backend** — there is no Next.js rewrite proxy like the public frontend uses. The backend URL comes from `NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL`.

### Page Structure

| Route | Component | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| `/` | `page.tsx` | Login |
| `/dashboard` | `Dashboard.tsx` | System overview, Redis stats |
| `/knowledge` | `KnowledgeCandidates.tsx` | Knowledge gap review and management |
| `/questions` | `QuestionLogs.tsx` | Recent question logs and analytics |

### Dashboard Components (map 1:1 to admin API endpoints)

| Component | Admin API |
|-----------|-----------|
| `UserStatistics` | `GET /api/v1/admin/users/stats` |
| `AbusePreventionSettings` | `GET/PUT /api/v1/admin/settings/abuse-prevention` |
| `BansThrottles` | `GET /api/v1/admin/redis/stats`, `POST clear-bans/clear-throttles` |
| `ResponseCacheManager` | `GET /api/v1/admin/cache/response/stats`, `POST response/clear` |
| `SuggestedQuestionsCache` | `GET/POST /api/v1/admin/cache/suggested-questions/*` |
| `KnowledgeCandidates` | `GET/PATCH/POST /api/v1/admin/knowledge-candidates/*` |
| `QuestionLogs` | `GET /api/v1/admin/llm-logs/recent` |

## Forbidden

- Never import from `frontend/` — these are completely separate applications
- Never use Shadcn CLI or assume Shadcn component APIs
- Never use fingerprint challenge auth — that is public-frontend-only
- Never proxy API calls through Next.js rewrites — call the backend directly
